participating-org.narrative:
Motto to Empower the Health, Education and Rights (MEHER) emergence is result of youth commitment to serve marginalized communities. MEHER was established in March 2003 by a dedicated and committed group of young professionals and it has been registered on 08th February 2005. Initial objective of MEHER establishment was to organize local communities for self-help approach for their communal development. MEHER was registered as non-profit NGO with sole purpose of serving the marginalized communities with the following objectives:
Capacity building of communities and organizations through trainings/workshops/seminars;
Facilitate provision of social services to underserved and un-served communities;
Facilitate and encourage local human resources for achieving their self-perceived objectives economically, effectively and efficiently;
Enhance women#s awareness about their rights, their reproductive rights; and workfor their own overall empowerment and development;
Pro-actively participate in the human rights activities; and
Disseminate Information, Education and Communication (IEC) awareness through different means, for instance, electronic and print media, handbills, poster, research and publications.
VISION:

Everyone in society lives a dignified life
MISSION:

MEHER struggles for the development andempowerment of communities through participatory approach interventions at grass-root level by safeguarding and promoting basic human rights, provision of basic needs, access to information and elimination of gender inequalities.
THEMATIC AREAS:
Health, Education, Sustainable Livelihood and Economic Opportunities, Disaster Risk Reduction, Women Empowerment with Gender Mainstreaming, Human Rights, WASH, Infrastructures, Environment, Relief and Rehabilitation, Capacity Buildings.
